\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid3021308 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Could you tell me how many years you lived in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Approximately two years. I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So when you were two you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Where did you move to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 To Bowling Back Lane - in Bradford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh - how long, let's see - it would be about twelve years I should imagine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Where did you move to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 From - from Bowling Back Lane to - Bowling Hall Road. To number sixty-three Bowling Hall Road. That's also Bradford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember why the family made these moves, do you remember why they moved from Halifax to Bradford?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh - well, yes, me dad worked for a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 boiler making}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  firm, and this firm came to Bradford to set up in business and he brought father with him as his first man. And that was why he came from Halifax to Bradford. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You moved from Bowling Back Lane Bradford, to Bowling Hall Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When you were about fifteen or sixteen were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, it would be, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember why you moved from Bowling Back Lane to Bowling Hall Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, be
cause - mother had died previously and - father had - inflicted a step-mother upon us. And the situation was anything but happy. And so we left - father and went to this address, my oldest sister having then got married. And we all lived together at this 
address.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So all four children moved out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 From your father and stepmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And you all moved into this rented house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 It was rented, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Your oldest sister got married about that time did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 She was married in 1914. Yes, yes, December 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you all lived together did you, with your sister's husband as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well all lived - yes. We all}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16583848\charrsid2561303 lived}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  together there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And you lived there until after 1919 did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Until 1919. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How many brothers and sisters did you have, could you tell me their birth order and spacing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 The - my oldest sister was born the - twenty-seventh of April - twenty-seventh of April - 1891.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What was she called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Elsie. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Elsie was the eldest then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Elsie was just the one name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Who came after Elsie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And then my brother was born in 1892. His name was Harold.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How much difference was there between Elsie and Harold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - Elsie was born in April as I say, twenty-seventh of April in 19 -1891. And Harold was born on the twenty-second of September, 1892.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So about eighteen months difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Who came after Harold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I came after Harold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How much younger were you than Harold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well he was born in 1892 and I was born in 1897. So there was over five years 'cos I was born in March you see, fifth of March. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And then you had a younger sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And then Doris was born in - 1892 - I don't know whether
 it was 1899 or - a hundred. I think it would be 1899 in November. November twenty-eighth 1899.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So she was about two years younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Two years younger than me, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When you were born your father was about thirty-three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Could you tell me where he came from, was he a Halifax man or did he come from somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 He was a Halifax man as you can see by that - his father's birth certificate there. You see, he was born at the address of his - at his g
rocer's shop, he was actually born at the Grocer's shop his father owned. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So that he'd always lived in Halifax?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes. That's right. Until he came to Bradford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Could you tell me what his occupation was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 He was a boilermaker. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did he have any other job before or after he became that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I've - oh only in his later years. He - he was still in it 'cos sort of engineering work because he worked on the trams. Not driving or conducting but with the mechanism of the trams you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 He was a sort of mechanic was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, that's right. Later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 But while you were a child he was always a boilermaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 boiler making}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 , yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember him ever doing any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Never, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Never. No. He was always fully employed. Yes, that was an - that was an amazing thing about it actually. He never - I never remember him being out of work. He might have - he stayed off on his own occasionally but - he was never unemployed. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And he was a boilermaker as far back as you can remember until about 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, I should think that's as near as we could get, you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When did he start working on the trams being a mechanic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 It would be about that same time, I - I think he would have made the change from the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 boiler making}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  to working on the trams about that same time, I should fancy that's as near as I can remember you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 About 1919, just after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, I should think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You don't know why he changed to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I've no idea. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Your mother was thirty-two when you were born wasn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Could you tell me where she came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - I think it was Barnsley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did she come to Halifax when she married your father or did she come to Halifax when she was a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well now that's what I don't know. No, I can't tell you that, I've no idea of it
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did she have any jobs before she married your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I only ever remember hearing her talk about being a weaver. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 
And I can remember the name of Hattersley looms being mentioned. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Now what kind of weaving they did on Hattersley looms I've no idea, because I've no knowledge of weaving trades at all. But
 - during my lifetime and when I was at school she did do part time laundry work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 She took washing in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh no, not at home, no, she worked at a laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And that was just part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. She used to always have Monday mornings hom
e and Friday afternoons and of course Saturdays. But during the midweek she worked at this laundry. And her job I know was doing the special kind of things, the things that needed special attention and - careful detail sort of. I know she was engaged on t
hat kind of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Sort of collars and tablecloths and that kind of thing do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well her might be - you see blouses, fine blouses of course were - worn at that time so - it would be that kind of thing she was engaged in there - working; there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So it was sort of part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 But Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday, would her hours be very long, do you know? Do you remember, did she go very early in the morning?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Now let me thing. She might have to be there for about half past seven. Seven thirty - and then I think she would be home about teatime.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So her hours were quite long?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 They were really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 She would work pretty well full time during the middle of the week, it was just Monday and Friday that she did sort of part time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 About how old were you when she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Fourteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Was that the only job that you can remember her doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Oh yes. Quite definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When your mother went out to work who looked afte
r the children? Or did she only do this work after you were old enough to look after yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well - we were - we were - it was while I was at the secondary school you see. And - Doris was only two years younger than myself so that - we were - at a reasonably capable age you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And perhaps Elsie would be old enough to take charge would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes, and - me father's work was quite near. And they used to have a mid morning break and he always popped in at that mid morning break, in home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So she never had anyone to look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh no. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Could you tell me how many rooms there were in the house at Bowling Back Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well there was one big living room, downstairs, and - a nice back kitchen. It was a through
 house. And - it had the old fashioned - set pot boiler as they used to call it with the fire underneath it, you know, for boiling the clothes and it was quite good actually although we hadn't hot and cold water. It was just cold water we had. And - we ha
d a cellar. And upstairs we just had one good big bedroom and a smaller one and a decent sized landing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Was there an attic at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. There was no attic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did anyone else besides your parents and brother and sisters live in the..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 There were no relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 The family washing was done at home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
My mother was - I - there's nothing I can say - I can't speak too highly of her altogether, in every possible way. She was absolutely admirable. She seemed to do everything, she made clothes and mended clothes, she did e
verything. And baked eternally. She never - we never bought anything to - to eat, it was always home made. Baking, cakes, pies and everything. In fact I - we have many time said that when I look back I don't know how on earth she managed it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Especially going out to work as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes. She went for part of the time mind, she didn't go out to work all the time you see. But - I was going to the secondary school you see and - I suppose she thought it was - a lift on the way. And Harold had gone to
 serve his apprenticeship in the Bradford trade, she wanted him to do }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16583848\charrsid2561303 well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
. Which he was done. He became director you see, of - of one of the firms - of the last firm he worked for. And - I consider I've done fairly well in me own field as well. I made considerable success actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Could you tell me, the clothes that you wore when you were still at school, would they be new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well they were never - I never wore anything bought from outside secondhand, but - mother did used to cut do
wn my oldest sister's clothes and do them for me you see. And in that way she kept us tidy and we wore one another's as we grew out of them and passed them down you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would she ever make you new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh definitely. Yes, definitely, quite definitely. And that's where I got first got my interest in sewing. I used to sit and watch, yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did she ever actually buy you any clothes or were they always made at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 They were - they were - I never remember her buying a single thing to wear. They were always made. Even underskirts and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16583848\charrsid2561303 knickers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  and - coats, she's made coats as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What about Harold's clothes, would she make his suits as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well no, I've no recollection - he was clothed certainly but I remember her ever making his clothes so they must have been bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What about shoes, do you remember your mother or father mending or making shoes for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 It was a job father always considered his responsibility to repair our shoes and he was constantly with the last mending shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would the shoes be new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh we always bought new shoes. In fact I can remember quite distinctly going to the shops to buy new shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember where they were bought, do you remember the shop you used to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes. There was a shop - in Wakefield Road and it was called Speights, and I think that shop has - still has got several branches around. Speights - shoes. Yes, I can - we got to know the lady there quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When would you get new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh, only when they were really needed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You wouldn't get them at a certain time of year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When would you get new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh always for Whitsuntide. Oh it was a regular thing to get new clothes for Whitsu
ntide. And of course a gym slip was a thing that was got - when it was needed. It - nothing to do with Whitsuntide clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you wear clogs as well as shoes at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I never wore clogs. The only clogs I can remember in our family }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 was}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 pair}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
 Harold got once. And - they were soon discarded because he hadn't been wearing them long when he sprained his ankle wearing them and so they were discarded and then no more clogs ever came.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh very much so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did he do any cleaning or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
He always had his own jobs, he always saw to the coal buckets being filled. He would make beds. He would help with the washing if he was available. And he would help with
 cooking and such things - we always had - things prepared in season. Red cabbage we always had - pickled cabbage when it - when the red cabbages became in - in season. He would do the job of cutting it all up and salting it ready for pickling. And doing 
onions for pickling, and all that kind of thing, he - it was - he took it as his responsibility.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And he'd make the fires in the mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you ever remember him doing any decorating or repairs or improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 He was decorating, yes, and mother too, I can remember her helping with paper hanging. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Was it your own house at Bowling Back Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, it was rented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did he ever dress, undress - bath you or read to you, did he ever help when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I can never remember him helping to bath us but - he did help in - in lots of ways and he would - he would prepare a meal and - he would - I can remember him taking us out for walks into the woods. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes. Yes. And - I don't know whether - I'm meandering on now, outside the point - he was very keenly interested at one time in the Quaker movement. And - we used to be taken there to any social functions they held which were quite considerable actually.
 And - we used to attend social functions at our own Sunday schools you see. Am I meandering off the point?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did he tell you stories, did he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes. Yes. Functions - yes. And mother would be there at those Quaker social functions as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did he ever look after you when she was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well he would be there if she had occasion to go out but - she never went out a lot. On her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh definitely, we all had jobs to do. My job - one of my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16583848\charrsid2561303 jobs}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  was dusting. And - a job I detested at the time was dusting the - it was an iron frame sewing machine that we had and I had to get into all those little curves and nooks and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 crannies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
 with the frames of the sewing machine. And - the chairs, you know, all the - oh she was very particular about getting into all the nicks and - and getting all the dust out. Yes, I had the job of dusting and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And your sisters had their own jobs did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes, they did as well. They helped with their jobs. Of course, my oldest sister, she was more responsible and she used to make cakes. She was older being that six years older all the time, yes, oh we were well trained at an e
arly age actually domestically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How long did you continue to do these tasks, did you continue after you left school for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well we had to you see and - you see, mother died when - when we were really - well I was fourteen and Elsie was tw
enty and Doris - twelve. She was - well actually she was eleven when mother died. But she would be twelve the same year, later on you see. We had to continue on I mean to say it was part of our make-up, we had to - we had to realize domestic responsibilit
ies and when we got into our own home away from - father and his - his second wife, we had it to do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you looked after the house yourselves once you moved into this other house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Can you tell me what Harold did when you were all still at home with your parents, do you remember Harold having a job of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well - I don't remember specifically any job inside the house, but he did used to do some shopping. On his way home, he - he worked in Bradford you see, a
nd it was quite a distance from where we were living and he used to do shopping in Bradford on his way home from work - but he was keenly interested in woodwork, he got his grounding at school you see, and he used to have a - a bench fitted up in this cel
lar at home and he used to go down there and - do woodwork and - he - I've - the knife box I'm using at the present time is one he made, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your little sister, Doris, do anything to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh she was very capable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What sort of jobs would she undertake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
She - oh she would do the washing up and dusting and - and of course we had a lot of bass at the fireplace we had - and copper. We used to do all that cleaning, helping to clean that you see and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did the older children help the younger with things they found difficult such as dressing or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well I don't remember - I don't remember being helped with eating because - me memory doesn't go back that far. But - Elsie, she was very keen on embroidery and - she taught 
me a lot. In - in - that way. And crochet work, she used to - she used to do that. she was very capable altogether really and - oh yes, she would lend a hand in - in anything, but I don't remember anything as far as dressing. Helping you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember helping the elder ones in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Let me think now. I just can't recall any specific - we all seemed to help in among helping each other you know but - I can't remember any specific - job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh my goodness, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you know what time it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16583848\charrsid2561303 Elsie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
 and Harold were older, Doris and I were sort of more of - of a - of an age and we sort of - we sort of grew up together more, Doris and I, being youn
ger. The other two were allowed out later you see. But they had to be in at a certain time. And if - if Elsie had gone to a church social and she wasn't home - mother would be off to that church to see what was amiss and bring her home you see. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed at night?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh I can't remember, I think we put ourselves to bed you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Then you don't know at what age you did start to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. I - I only remember going to bed and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you share your bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh yes, we - as a matter of fact Elsie and Doris and I, we all slept in one big bed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Where would Harold sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Harold slept - he had to sleep in the same room, a distance aw
ay, so it was quite a big room - and he had to use that room and a single bed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And your parents had the other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What room - did you bath in at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 We had no bathroom, no. We had to use - we had to have it in front of the fire in the living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you have some sort of zinc bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes. Yes. And - yes, and Friday night was bath night for Doris and I and I don't know when the others had theirs, they'd wait until we'd all gone to bed I suppose. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So it would be Friday night usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh - at bath time. Each week. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 The meals? In this - in this room, we had just the one bi
g living room you see and we had the table in centre and that's where we had the meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you didn't have it in the kitchen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh no. No. In this big room. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room, perhaps in the kitchen for some reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well it would only be on a very rare occasion because - there was no heating in there you see. And - the - this set pot that I've told you about, it was a huge thing and it had a - a huge board made to fit the top - exactly and -
 it made a huge table you see. So that it - it was very useful for - kitchen working you know in there,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Your mother would bake on there would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, and - it was a lovely scrubbed - scrub, we used to clean it, lovely white boarded top you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What - where did your mother cook, she cooked in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
In that kitchen, yes. Except the oven - was in the living - in this living room you see. Yes, the fireplace there, the oven, it was one - not a gas oven you see. It was - part of t
he range and she did all the cooking in that oven. But she could prepare things in that kitchen you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So she didn't have a gas cooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Could you tell me when breakfast was eaten when you were all at Bowling Back Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes, yes. Oh well, we were - dad started work at - at half past six. And he used to come in at - eight o'clock to half past for a breakfast break. You see. But we used to - used to get our breakfast quite early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 About eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would most of you be there, would the elder children be there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes. 'Cos that would give Harold time to - he had to walk to Bradford you see to his work. Yes, I should say roughly about eight o'clock and - my oldest sister, she was working in the 
mill, and - she used to have an hour - a half hour break for breakfast as well you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So that everybody would be there for breakfast at eight?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What would you have to eat and drink at breakfast time - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Now 
then - do you know I - no, I just can't remember, I can't remember quite what we had to drink. It would be - a cup of tea I think. I can't remember - we should have bread and butter, I know we - we didn't have cooked breakfasts every morning, I'm quite su
re of that. Bread and butter and - something to spread on it. I couldn't say what. Might have been honey, but I was never keen on money though. The others might have been but I wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What about on special days such as Sundays, would you have anything at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Might have had a boiled egg. And then we always had a - a cooked roast, we used to have a big joint of meat cooked at Sunday. Yes, and - Yorkshire puddings and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 That was Sunday lunchtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What time would you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
On a Sunday? Any day. Oh - oh well now, - you see I'm a little bit confused because part of the time mother was working and part of the time she was at home and when she was at home I used to come home from school for - for a m
idday lunch and I - it would be half past twelve when I'd get home. So that would be the time for the midday lunch. 'Cos I just had time to have it and get back to school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you have to make it as well?
