e dad dropped on me like a ton of bricks. Where have you got that chalk from? I said, I got it from school. He says, where have you got it from school? So I had to tell I'd got it out of the cupboard. I never was more frightened in my life. Mother threate
n
ed to come to school and tell the headmistress. Every footstep I heard coming up that schoolyard I was sure it was mother coming to tell the headmistress. They never knew the torture they'd inflicted on me by that. They didn't hit me for it. But it was th
at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 mental}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
 torture I endured. And those three sticks of chalk rested on the mantelshelf until they were nearly black. And me dad said, if you touch those chalks - he says, you'll know about it. I daren't have touched those chalks for all the tea in China.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 They didn't ask you to take them back to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
No. And - no, because I think they would have really put me in disgrace. Mother says, you've been given a position of trust, they've elected you as monitor because they think they can trust you.
 And then you do that Oh gosh, it - do you know, nobody ever knew the torture I endured with that. And I never stole the weight of a pin in me life after. No, it taught me a lesson once and for all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So this was the worst punishment you ever got really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh definitely. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16583848\charrsid2561303 Oh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How did you feel about it, did you resent your parents for it or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I always - no, I wouldn't say that I resented them but - because I knew I'd deserved it. I knew I shouldn't have done it when it
 was brought home to me and it must have been just on the spur of the moment. I mean, I wasn't in the habit because I was too scared stiff of the teachers at school. All children at that time were scared stiff of teachers at school. I - it was just that s
he'd got this chalk and I hadn't any. If she'd given me one of her sticks of chalk that would never have happened. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a more important part than 
the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, I should think they - they both - they both tried to keep us in the straight and narrow, both of them, oh yes.
