Well my oldest sister took lessons. But the piano was bought - because - all the family of us went on a holiday to Carnforth and we had - we stayed at a lovely old farmhouse and
 at this farmhouse they had a piano. And it just attracted me like a - like a magnet. And by the time I came away I could play one tune. And of course me dad's sister, as I said before, she was a pianist and - at this he must have thought I was going to f
ollow suit and of course it pleased him greatly because he was so fond of music himself. And from then on he started }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 saving}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
 up to buy this piano. And he showed me - all these golden sovereigns, he set them in a row on the table and there must have been a lo
t because they extended a long way. And he'd saved up these golden sovereign to buy these piano. And - Elsie took lessons but I never did because I was - at this secondary school and he offered me the chance to take lessons, I can never say I hadn't the c
hance, but I said, no, I've enough with me homework, I can perhaps do that after. And - so that I never did get lessons and of course later then mother died you see and of course the opportunity never came.
