\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Going on - I don't remember. No, I've no recollection }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 For holidays you went for about four days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would it be regularly you would go, would it be every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Oh not every year. But - we did go a few times to Morecambe, we never went further than Morecambe, and that holiday I've explained before about - to Carn - forth to that farm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How long did you stay at Carnforth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I think we stayed about a week when we went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 But otherwise most of your holidays were at Morecambe were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, we could play in the sand and we enjoyed that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Which members of the family went, did all six of you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well 
I can remember just - dad staying at home and mother going with the four of us. But - he has gone as well, as - me dad's gone as well at times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Why would it be that he would stay at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I've no idea. I've no idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Because he was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, it would be just his - his own fancy I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you always go to Morecambe or do you remember going anywhere else other than Morecambe and that time you went to Carnforth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well we went to - I know we went - we went several times to Morecambe, no, I've no recollection of going anywhere else, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When you were on holiday do you remember what you'd do when you were there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Mostly went for walks, oh yes, we used to go walks. And - if there was any music, which there often use
d to be, brass bands you know and we'd sit and listen to that, play with a ball around you know. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Saturdays? Well I have some recollection of going out with mother on a Saturday aft
ernoon. Not every Saturday afternoon but sometimes. And - I could have been doing homework either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You did homework from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. I can - if I'd any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You don't remember going out on a Saturday evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well unless it was a concert at church or - some social function like that at church, that's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You said you sometimes went to Quakers social functions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would they be on a Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How about Sundays, you've already told me you went to Sunday school in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, it was church all day Sundays. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you have any different clothes for Sunday, did you have best clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh yes, definitely, you - oh we always kept Sunday clothes for Sunday, you know, weekend clothes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you wear them on Saturday as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 If we were going anywhere special, but that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 If you did go anywhere special where would it be to on a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well, to these Quaker - you see, with the Quakers. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You 
said you sometimes used to visit people at Halifax with your elder sister? Would you go on a Saturday on these outings would it be during school holidays or when?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 It would be during the summer holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you ever play games at home on a Saturday or Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - I can't remember playing games except with a ball perhaps just in the back you know. Throwing the ball around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 We were not allowed to do a thing on Sundays
. I've sneaked upstairs to do a bit of sewing myself on a Sunday. We weren't allowed to even sew on a Sunday, it was six days shalt thou labour, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So how did you fell about Sunday, did you think it was a fairly dull day at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh very much so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well - as I say, mother and dad - she went to the Quakers because he did. She was brought up Church of England like we were brought up Church of England. But she went t
o the Quakers with him because - he was interested and I suppose she thought if she didn't go he may not either and it was an interest which he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Had he been brought up as a Quaker or had he acquired this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 He'd acquired it I fancy, but I couldn't say that definitely, but I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 fancy}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  he had acquired it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How often would your parents go to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - when - when he was really in with it he - it used to be every Sunday afternoon. The two of them. And after - after we'd come out of 
Sunday school at our church of England we used to go and meet them then from - and all walk home together you see. Yes, from the meeting - from the Quakers meeting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So that would be most Sundays at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You still carried on going to the Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You went to a Sunday school in the morning and afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And church at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well at Whitsuntide there used to be the usual Whits
untide treat. And - at Shrove Tuesday they - there was always the annual Shrove type tea, but there was no outing, it was a tea and concert held in the schoolrooms you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What would the Whitsuntide treats be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh well, we used to go to a field 
- that - which was booked you see for this - for all these games, there were games arranged, competing - for prizes you know, and then we used to get a bun and tea. At these Whitsuntide fields. And the youngest ones used to be taken in a - in a cart - in 
a cart drawn by horses, with sides up you know and they used to stand all in this and be taken to the field.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you have a band or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, sometimes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you belong to the choir at church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, because it was all male choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What other social activities were organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well - well they used to have - plays and we used to take part in those. And - then they used to have - in the wintertime from time to time they'd have - an evening - a Saturday evenin
g dance. With - a vocalist - perhaps one of the choir members would sing one or two items you see. That was the kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did the church run any temperance club at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, I don't recall - the Church of England running a temperance c
lub. But - in connection with the Quakers, they used to have their - some of their concerts in what was Bradford's temperance hall at the time. And - but I don't remember any - they did used - there were plenty of temperance lectures given in different pa
rts I know, but - but I don't remember going, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church or chapel, was there Girl guides at that time or the Girls Brigade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I was never in any - I don't think so. No, I've - there used to b
e for the boys, there was football clubs and cricket teams. But I've no recollection of anything for - for girls, beyond these operatic interests you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. No, I don't remember any family prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your father take an interest in politics at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well only slightly - but he did have some interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Either Liberal or Conservative, I don't think it would be Labour. I fancy Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Why do you think he held those views or do you not know enough about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I couldn't say, I mean - I've no idea what - what his idea - he
 was a working man and I suppose his interest would be where the - working man was going to derive any benefit you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your mother have any political views at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well if she did she never - never aired them, no. Not that I can recall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember your father or mother - your mother died before women got the vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember your father ever voting in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh definitely, always used to vote, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you happen to know what he party he voted for, you said he was a Liberal you though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I think it would be Liberal. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure, to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I never heard any such views aired and - he did always seem to be on quite easy terms with his boss. 'Cos we knew his as children - we knew the bosses of this firm he worked for. We knew them quite well you see, they always used to speak to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Was your father a member of a political party at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Not that I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You don't remember him working for a party at an election at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. Oh no, me mother never did, 'cos she wouldn't have had time anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Not that I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
No, well mother never did have any spare time, you see, she - her time was always preoccupied with - as I say making and mending and doing everything that was necessary. And - and of course me dad too, I mean, he s
pent plenty of time repairing shoes and - any odd jobs in the house he would - pay attention to you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you don't remember him having any other interests other than his pigeons then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, he was a bit interested in fishing, I know when we we
nt on that holiday to Carnforth he - he went with a friend, I think they must have been staying somewhere in the near vicinity, and I know they went to Silverdale fishing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your mother have any interests outside the home, would she have time for any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, I can't say that she had because - she - she was really fully occupied - practically twenty-four hours of the day, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When did your father get home from work in the evenings, I think you said about half past five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh all of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 He wouldn't go out at all during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember your father ever attending any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh he attended pubs - when spirit moved him, but never - I never remember him attending any clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would he attend a pub regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 It just depends. There were stretches of his time - when he was thoroughly a hundred percent teetotal. But then he would have another s
pasm when he would - go frequently you see. And - I could never understand him that way because he was so strong willed that he could leave drink alone entirely and severely. But yet he would then have other spells when he would - just go, you know, when 
he wanted to go, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would it be say every night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, he could have gone every night or - or - and - and weekends when it was that side out you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you think it was because he was depressed in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well, you can never tell you see, I mean, when you're so young you don't realize what they're attitude is - about things
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your mother ever go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Not that I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your father take part in any sport, you said he liked fishing when he was at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 Carnforth?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did he do any other sort of sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well not - no, I don't think I can remember him doing anything in the way of sport. Oh - he did swim. Oh yes, he did swim, he liked swimming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would he go swimming quite frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well - I don't know about quite frequently, but when they were young at home - they - it was every Sunday morning before breakfast they all were made to go to the baths to swim. He was a very good swimmer actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You all went, you mean your father took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Me father's family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You mean his family before he was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 He used to go with his parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. And he was keen for us too to swim and I could swim quite well when I was small and when we went on one o
f the holidays to Morecambe with us I remember he took me out and - the tide was in - and we swam out as far as the end of the pier. Just he and I. And then he says, well you've come a long way now so climb on my back and I'll ride you back. Which he did.
 So you can tell he was a reasonably good swimmer to do like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did he ever attend the races, horse races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I never remember him attending a horse race but I do know that he would have an occasional shilling on a horse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So he would have an occasional bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes, it would only be small bets. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs such as a boot club or a sick club or a funeral club, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well they would pay insurance, you know, I mean I don't know whether that applies to what you're - getting at. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What sort of insurance would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 A funeral expenses insurance, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So that if anyone died everything was paid for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 That's right. Well, you got so much you see, 
whether it covered what you wanted to pay for or what I don't know. They - you can take out an insurance policy for a certain fixed amount you see. And - at the time that person insured dies well you get that amount of money and it's up to you to make it 
go as far as it will.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would they be a member of the sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 
I suppose he would be a member of a sick club, I don't know definitely, but I should fancy if there was anything like that going on at work, he would be a member of it.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How did you get on with your brother and sisters, was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, we were very - all very friendly together, we all got on very well together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 As a child who did you play with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 mainly,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  your brother and sisters or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well Doris and I were sort of - we - we were more of an age you see than the two older ones and we played together quite a lot. And we did have children round about we used to play with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You said you used to have about six in to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, for - when it was a party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were they people who lived nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. And perhaps one or two school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 friends you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When you played out where would you play, in the yard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well in the yard or - there were some fields quite close, we
 could go play there if we wanted or - sometimes we'd play may I cross the water - please may I cross the water and we used - some at one side and some at the other side of the road but - you see, there wasn't the traffic then that there is now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you ever play in other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 ' homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Occasionally, but not very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What other games did you play at that time, anything that was popular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well at that time diabolo was very popular. Yes. It was - you'd a handle in each hand connect
ed by a piece of rope, fine rope, and a diabolo cone which was - wide at each end and tapered narrow to the centre and you'd to - to balance that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 cone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  on this string and work it - and you could swing it up and it could go as high as the telephone wires and catch it again as it came down and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You did it with both hands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes. Oh I got quite expert at that. It was very popular. And then of course at - at - in the springtime there was always - shuttlecock and battledore. And - marbles. We used to pl
ay marbles on the pavement, then we'd a bouncer and four checks, you know. That was - and whip and top. Those were games we used to play. Yes, butterscotch we had - hopping into flags, yes, hopscotch, yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were you free at that time to play with anyone you pleased or were your parents particular who you played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - they always knew who we were playing with but - there couldn't have been anybody they objected to or they would have said I think.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I suppose we must have got dirty, although I can't remember how badly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You don't remember your parents discouraging you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, I've no recollection of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Youth organisations? No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you have any hobbies when you were at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - if you like to call them hobbies, but I think what I did was quite closely bound up with what I was doing at school. I
 used to be fond of painting. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would that be water colours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes. Water colours, I'd no oils at that time. And - of course needlework was always a first love with me, you see, I could always - I was always making something. Either dolls clothes or - something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You did embroidery as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And embroidery, yes. Oh yes, I used to love to do embroidery and crochet work, we used to - make }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 antimacassars}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  at that time in - long strips of crochet work and then the - the three long strips wer
e joined together by another - criss - cross arrangement, I've forgotten how now. And I often used to spend time doing that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you keep any pets at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh - only pussy. Only a pussy, we had a pussy called Topsy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you help to look after her at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I won't say - I don't think I was ever qualified to look after - not in the way from health - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 hygiene}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  point of view but - we did used to be very fond of this cat you know and nurse a her and - and that sort of thing,
 but I - I don't remember ever brushing her or anything like that, I suppose the others used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you ever collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You mean perhaps in the way of stamps or anything like that? One thing I did used to collect would be - littl
e specimens of plants and stick them between pages of a book to press them you see. Yes, I've done that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And you did some gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes, I - I had that little garden patch
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh with a little - with a fishing net. Oh - only very occasionally, but I can say that I have done it and put them in a glass jar you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You've already told me you went walks with your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you ever go bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I never possessed a bicycle 'cos my 
mother would never let me have one. Me brother had one and I used to say, why on earth can't I have one when he's got one? And all she thought, she says, yes, well you wouldn't have it five minutes, you'd go and break your neck on it. So I never got one.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Just - connected with school that's all, I used to play hockey. Yes, with school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And you used to swim?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Swim, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you swim for the school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes - well I never swam in any c
ompetitions you know but - I remember when I was at the elementary school I - I remember one particular morning I had to go - I - I'd swum the length that morning for the first time and I had to go and tell the headmistress I'd done it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 ever}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
 go to any theatres or concerts or music halls or cinemas while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well now theatres were a thing that were rather excluded, I remember we were doing - Julius }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 Caesar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  at school and it was being played in Bradford but - and a party from the class were going to see Julius }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 Caesar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 , but I wasn't allowed to go. It was quite outside - our range, the theatre going wasn't for children and - in our days, so I want allowed to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 It wasn't because they couldn't afford it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 W
ell, I suppose it might have been one factor, but at the same time if they could have had money - theatres they thought were quite wrong for young children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So the only concerts and entertainments you went to would be at church and at the Quaker meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
At church, yes, and I remember going to - because I was older then - I went to - I don't know which one it was - Flora Dora or one of the - Flora Dora or the Geisha - or the Quaker Girl, it was one of those I went to see but I should be much old
er - in - and left school. No. I'd left school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You never went to the cinema while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I only remember once going to the cinema and it must have been when they were first started and the lady next door took me. I think she
 must have got a free pass, - and she took me. I've no recollection at all of what the picture was, I wasn't awfully interested.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your parents give you any pocket money at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh very little. But we did get it regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes. And on this we used to have a bank book at school. The Yorkshire Penny Bank it was at that time. And we used to save a penny or tuppence of this money we got - I think we got about threepence, and we used to save this and that used to accumul
ate and by the time summer holidays came there was just about enough to pay our railway fare for holidays you see. Yes. And that's what it was put in the Yorkshire Penny Bank for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you have any money left after putting it in the bank, would you save a penny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well perhaps a penny we'd have to buy a few sweets, but that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Is that where the money went, on sweets usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, or - I - I've often bought an apple with my - even though we had apples at home we always used to get pl
enty of fruit provided but - I frequently bought an apple with my spare money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 
You said you did embroidery, I should imagine embroidery silk would be quite expensive then, who would pay for that, would it be your mother or would you have to buy that out of your spending money?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well, I suppose mother would provide what was necessary for that kind of thing you see, I don't remember having to - having to buy it myself you see, it would be bought out of - she would provide what was needed, I mean, sh
e'd see the interest there then would do everything to encourage it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after the house and the family, such as a relation or friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. We had one good neighbour, when mothe
r was poorly she frequently came to visit her. But I never remember her doing anything, she simply came and sat you see. But I don't remember her doing anything at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 She came in to keep your mother company when she wasn't very well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage, how did the family manage when she was confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well that was where my career was spoilt. That was where I came into it. I - you see, my oldest sister was working and earnin
g a wage. I was the next one. And at an age where I was capable of doing something so - I had - one or two spells off school which were very detrimental to me you see. And - I was the one to do the looking after her you see. And seeing to things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you have to sort of housekeep at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Oh definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You were only fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I should be thirteen - not thirteen. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 Quite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 . Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How long was she ill for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Two years altogether. She started quite suddenly one Sunday 
morning and they used to go to an allotment on a Sunday morning, they could buy rhubarb and that kind of thing you see, and flowers they used to get - from the allotments. And she started quite suddenly one morning while they were out, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 stricken}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  with this p
ain around her - heart. And that was how she started and it got - from that gradually worse and worse. And it was valvular heart disease that she'd got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Was she in bed for the whole of that two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Not the whole of that time, oh no, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 not}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  by an
y means. She was - she was only in bed for the last - we had the bed downstairs, a single bed downstairs for her actually - I can't remember the exact length of time she was in bed. But it was a few weeks. And - of course I could do the house - then my ol
d
est when she came from work - she could see to any personal requirements of mother's, she was older than I was you see and she could deal with her - as a patient, you know what I mean, more than I could. But I could see to - giving her drinks and what was
 necessary you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So how old were you when she started to be ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I'd only be - I'd be about eleven wouldn't I. Yes. I was fourteen when she died. No, I should be twelve wouldn't I - I should be twelve when she first started - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you would have finished school then would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well I had to leave you see. I had - well, as a matter of fact, I'd won the scholarship you see, to the High School - and - I had these periods. I - I'd - the full first year was - wasn't interrupted at all
, or the second. But the third year was interrupted with two spells, I know one was a month I was off at one stretch. And - of course at that time we didn't know how long she was going to go on like this you see. And - so they allowed me to }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 relinquish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  the scholarship. To stay at home. And I remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How long should you have attended that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I should think perhaps another year. And then if I'd been wanting to go on I should have - I should have been able to if I qualified you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you missed a full year's schooling in fact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes. And - although mind you - I was - at that time, at an elementary school they could enter what was called a labour examination and they were allowed to leave at thirteen, provided they passed this examin
ation. Well I was thirteen. And - I don't ever remember going in for that examination but I was allowed to leave, so they must have thought I was knowledgeable enough to leave. But I always remember the - me form mistress saying, I'm sorry to see you go. 
B
ut, she said, I suppose they need you at home. And that was it. And I was sorry to go because - I loved every minute of school and I'd gone with the determination that I was going to be a teacher. And you see - to gain a scholarship at that time, it was q
uite something. Because they were few and far between, most students at secondary schools were fee paying pupils. And I was the only girl in that school that year to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Most children at that time kept on at elementary school until they were thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. And left - and left the elementary school, they didn't - go on to secondary education at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You won't remember about when your sister was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, I've no knowledge of that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your parents have any relatives at all living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your parents have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
There was just one couple that I know used to - they used to come to my house but I don't know how frequently they went to their house, you see what I mean. But I do remember this particular couple coming and - spending an evening at our house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And you think they would probably go and visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 They might have gone there but I have no recollection of being left - while they went out you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your mother and father share the same friends, this couple were joint friends were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, I - oh yes, yes, it was - yes, it was a joint affair, you know, the two men and the two - ladies you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your mother have any friends of her own other than this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I n
ever remember her having any body - particular you know. If you mean like going out with another lady, you see, well there was nothing like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did she have any friends who sort of lived next door or anything like that, you said there was a lady who used to come in and sit with her?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, she used to come and sit, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, now you ask me that - I've very vague recollections - of hardly ever seeing one. Except if
 we happened to be in Bradford you could see them around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 But not in your neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 But not in the immediate vicinity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When you were naughty did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I never remember that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you won't have any knowledge of how policemen treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. None.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Your home was rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you see anything of your landlord at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, he used to call every Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 For his rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, for his rent. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 He was very gentlemanly, he was an Alderman of the City of Bradford and he was a real - really gentlemanly type of man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you have any feelings about him - were you in awe of him, you were never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 
afraid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  of being turned out of your house or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Oh never, no, and his wife was friendly with mother too, I mean, he - he used to come and do add - tiny repairs to the house himself. And - while he was doing such jobs mother would make him
 a cup of tea. And I always remember his wife - she gave - made her a blouse or something - in appreciation of - for what she'd done you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh yes. There - there was never a - a lot of surplus money you know. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What did you think about that at that time? Did you have any feelings about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - you could notice other children at school who you were obviously were very well off and you could notice th
at they came in lovely clothes specially made for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 school wear}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 , and you could feel the difference there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you notice at the secondary school perhaps more than the elementary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Oh I never noticed at the elementary school, it was at the secondary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Where you got the fee paying students?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What difference did it make to the family if your father was ill, but he never really was ill was he to be off work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. He was - he did have a - an operation once but - it sort of passed by without causing any disturbance you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 It didn't make you short of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh no, it passed by without any sort of - he might have had his wage paid to him, I don't know you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You weren't short?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
When there was someone in the district where you lived whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it, and do you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh no, I never remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You don't remember there ever being anyone who was disapproved of in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. No. Not at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 It never occurred at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I've no recollection of anything like that happening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You were never given any lessons by your parents or a tutor or a governess at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I think I must have been - not much more than two. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 
I must have been - very young, I think about threeish at - at the very most. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you go full time or just in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. No, I went all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What time would you finish in the evening, you'd start at nine o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Nine o'clock, yes, it would be. Half past three I should think in the afternoon you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What kind of a school was it that you went to, an elementary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Just an elementary school, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would it be a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh it was a board school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And it was a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Was it mixed, boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh well, as a matter of fact it was only across the road. So I just went across he road, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Who went with you, who took you to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well at that time you see, both my elder sister and brother were both going so I presumably - they would go with me you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you go home for your midday meal, at first your mother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  at home and made your meal for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And then later you used to go and meet her at the mill didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. The laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And have sandwiches with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I enjoyed every minute of my school life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What was this school called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 This - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 first one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  was Bowling Back Lane school. Yes. Bowling Back Lane Board School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How did you feel about the teachers there, were they all right or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 They were very nice, but, as I say, as young children in our day - we were always we sort of looked up to teachers 
as somebody - really out of this world and you just sort of held them in awe all the time you see. But at the same time - most of them were very kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, such as manners and tidiness, punctu
ality, ways of speaking, do you remember these things being emphasised at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well punctuality very much so. And cleanliness. Yes, cleanliness too
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you mean that your hands had to be clean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Your hands had to be clean and clean about your person as far as it was possible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did they ever say anything about your ways of speaking, did they object to you having a Yorkshire accent at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I never remember any objections to my speech at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen, how would they punish the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Send them outside the classroom door. And then of course they were living in fear and trembling for fear the headmistress should see them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 If she should what would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well they'd be taken to her room and severely chastised I suppose. I never got that treatment fortunately, so I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you think that some of them were given the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh yes, they would get the cane. I only had the cane
 once and it was because - on one particular day had said specifically, any single one of you who are late tomorrow morning will get the cane. And it just - happened that my youngest sister that morning, she was the world's worst and we had to drag her to
 school. And it made us, Elsie and I, both that minute late. And we both got the cane. And we were never late for school, but on that occasion we just - were unfortunate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So they got the same treatment as the boys, everyone got the cane if necessary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes. Mind you - I'm saying they were mixed, they were in the very lower forms, at the infants school, but - when it got higher up there was a separate boys school and a separate girls school you see, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh yes, very much so, yes, when we did well they were very pleased.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, they were very interested all the way along, with all of us. And they were interested with reports
 and what we were doing in exams and - oh yes, they were very keenly interested and want - they were really pleased when we were doing well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did they ever visit the school and meet the teachers at all, did they have open days or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I've no - I don't recall any open days for parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not when you were at the elementary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I think they were more or less the same, Anne.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You were all sort of working class people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Definitely working class, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - I think it's human nature to have some favourites really. And there might have been a - an od
d one or two who were favourites you know, but I think by and large they were all treat more or less alike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were there any gangs or groups in the school do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I've no recollection of any. Of any kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember there being any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you go another school afterwards, you went to the secondary school didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. I went - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What was that called?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 The Hanson Girls Secondary School. Hanson - Girls Secondary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What age were you when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I won me scholarship, I sat the exam when I was only ten. I'd been put up twice in one year at the elementary school, I must have been too bright and they - I was doing, you know, had to do the wo
rk for the higher standard. And it made me take that exam a year younger than the other - the average you see. So that I - I was going to the secondary school a year younger than I should have been normally you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So how old were you when you went, ten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I took the exam in the early - part of that year, I should be - ten in the - at that September and I'd be eleven the following March. The first March I was at the Secondary school I was eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What did you think of school when you moved there, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I - loved it. It never bored me at all, I loved every minute of it and I used to come home gaily and I used to love doing me homework. I used to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 puzzled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  and fuddled with it sometimes naturally like all children but still - I did love it and it was my sole ambition to stay at school and be a teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you think you preferred going to school even more then than you had done at Bowling Lane School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, because I liked it so much all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What were the teachers like at this secondary school, did you still quite like them or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well - there was one teacher I always felt had a bit of a - grudge against me somehow, I don't know - I might have been entirely wrong. But on the whole I found them all very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What about punishment at the secondary school, was it similar to that meted out at the other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well, I must confess that I never got any - but I suppose for those who did it would be the - similar, you know, to what the others got.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And your parents still took an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 At this Hanson Girls School did you find that the other children came from similar types of home to your won or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh yes, but there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 plenty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  of other
s who were well to do children, who were obviously well to do children you see. And you could see that in the way they were dressed. But there were plenty - in fact there were - there were one or two girls who went on maintenance grant. They received mone
y each week for be - to be at that secondary school you see. I wasn't on a maintenance grant, I received money. But I had gone on a free scholarship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And there were some children who had this to help their parents out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, they received this maintenance grant - I don't know how much the amount was. But it was a little that would be a help I've no doubt.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you say at the secondary school that the teachers treated he children in all the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh - oh yes. Yes, it made no difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you say there were any groups of girls, was it an all girls school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 All girls, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were there any groups of girls in the school who sort of kept together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I don't know, we all seemed - you know, we all seemed free and easy with each other. No, never felt sort of out of it in any way.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were there any children there who you think were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I never noticed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You didn't go to another school after that, how old were you when you left school altogether, when you finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well it - I must have been their - yes, I must have been thirteen and - left after I was thirteen you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you have stayed longer had you had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh quite definitely it would never have entered me head to leave. Except in the circumstances at home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you attend any part time education afterwards, such as evening classes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Not at that time. But - in later year of course I - I did. Quit consider - quite a bit you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would this be before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh no, late - much - no, oh no, since I've been married it's been - since I've been -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Simply that I wasn't able to stay on as I'd intended to at first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you think you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 benefited}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh - yes, most certainly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means or earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Could you tell me what was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I went apprentice to dressmaking you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How old were you when you started this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - I started that same summer so I should be - about thirteen and a half you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And you were an apprentice dressmaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. For a shilling a week. For the first year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember what hours you worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I certainly do. Eight o'clock at morning. Until half past seven at night. With an hour at lunchtime - and half an hour at half past four for a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You worked 'til half past seven every night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
And all those hours. And Saturday afternoon until four o'clock. And that for a shilling a week. And out of that shilling I got an extra penny pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And the rest went to the household budget?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Into the household - yes, you know, the budget.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How did you manage to get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh well, it was advertised and mother took me. She went with me for interview you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What exactly did you do in this job when you were an apprentice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well for one thing, I - I used to have to sweep the floor, you see, first thing at morning. Have the rooms all tidy for the - for everybody to start work. Keep the machines }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 dusted}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  down and - but then - I was - I - I excelled in needlework 
at school actually and - they must have seen that and they were - it - they were not - they wasted no time in putting me to needlework you see, they got a really good shillings worth out of me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you were quickly sewing and doing what the skilled people were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How long was the apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well - I didn't stay the full apprenticeship, I mean to say because - you see, after that - mother died and all this - difficulty at home had arisen and we were planning to go into this home of our own and - I always remember there was a - an advert from 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 Howard\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
 in one of the papers and it was a dress and I copied this dress and made it up for me older sister. And everybody was - who knew us, was so struck by the success of this th
at they used to say, well if you can make a dress for us like that you could make one for me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
 from that - I made things for people and earned extra money at home you see. And - that was it. Then of course we went to live on our own and - and I - that started me making things up at home and that's what I've been doing ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You've worked for yourself ever since?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Ever since you were about sixteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Seven - seventeen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When you were actually working at this sewing shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How many people were employed there, was it a very large place?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Oh very small, no, it was a - it was a local place actually, and there would be about - I shouldn't think more than half a dozen at the most. But - when - when it was out of season there were fewer you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When you were an apprentice you were only paid a shilling a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you feel that that was a fair wage or not at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I don't know, I suppose it was the accepted thing 
at the time you know but - it was certainly not much, it was just a matter of pocket money really wasn't it you see. No more than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you ever get any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, never. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh quite well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were there other apprentices there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
They were all - yes, at the time I was apprenticed I was the youngest you see. Then later on another young girl came and took my place you see, but - that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What was your employer, was it a lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
A lady. Yes. Actually there were two sisters. And - but one was the main one in the firm. It was just a small - firm really, you know, it was nothing like, I mean, going to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 Marshall\rquote s}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  in Bradford or anywhere like that you see, it was just - just a small firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How did the lady who employed you treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh quite well, she was very nice, she was a - a very - a very well educated lady actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh I enjoyed it. I enjoyed it all the time. I was very observant and picked a lot up that I was never shown, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What jobs have you done since the first world war, you've already told me that you've always worked for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, I've never worked in anything else but - but sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Have you ever finished work }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 altogether}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  or have you always done some sort of sewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well right up to be - turned seventy I've done something you see. But - the biggest change I made, I ever made, was when I went in fo
r the exam for a teacher's certificate and I - I took a concentrated two year course for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
. And I was lucky to get a first class teachers certificate. And I was also}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303  highly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
 commended for the practical work. And then the examiner, the City and Guilds exa
miner said to me, would - wouldn't you like to take the tailoring exam? I said, I've never thought about it. She says, well I would like to see you take that next year. I said, well I might think about it. Which I did, and I entered it. And I - when I got
 the result of that I'd got prize standard in that - City and Guilds. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you were able to teach then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh I was able to teach, yes, from the - from the getting the first teachers certificate you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How old were you when you got your teachers certificate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Forty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you teach full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Oh part time. But I taught for - from being forty-five - to sixty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 During those fifteen years did you teach just evening classes or day classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, I took some day t
ime work as well 'cos actually I was looking for two - separate - people actually. One was the Shipley Technical College and the other was - the needlework section of the Nursery Nurses Training course and that was taken during the day you see. Friday mor
nings and - Monday afternoon. Yes, that was what I did. For the nursery nurses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 At that time you carried on having your workroom, you were still taking in work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Oh - yes, I was doing both - doing both jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 At one time you employed people didn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes I did. Never more that - three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When was that? About how old would you be when you did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh let me see now - the last - the last I employed was in 1940 and she left because the war was on and she was in her own
 job she could - she was able to drive a car and she could drive a laundry van which saved her having to be called up you see. And she left. That was the last person I employed. So that was 1940, I should be - oh perhaps thirty-five, when I was employing 
about three people, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you've always been self employed and at one time employing others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You served a sort of apprenticeship didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. And you see - actually with this situation arising as it did for us domestically -
 I realized that sewing had to be my livelihood. It was my only means of earning a living you see, at that time. And so of course I got me head into it and made the most possible out of it. It was all I could do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you think you would have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes, I would have preferred teaching if I could have gone on from the start as I'd intended. Because that was in me bones when I took the teachers certificate at that later age, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You still wanted to teach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you quite enjoyed doing the teaching part of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, none whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you take part - you weren't a member at all were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among the workers at that time some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel that or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - the only thing that I did 
feel and which did sort of - I won't say ruffled me, but I just did feel it was a point - to raise objection on, was this. That I'd worked in this needle trade from being young and served what apprenticeship I was able to you see, but others could come in
 
and take the teachers course and just receive what treatment in the needle trades could be available during that two years period of teacher training. Whereas I had a life's experience of it and they could come in and take the same salary for the job as I
 was getting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh I don't think so. No, it didn't seem to make any difference to me at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When you were at home with your parents were friends ever }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 invited}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Your own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. And my sister's friends and - oh yes, they came frequently. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 And your parents friends, you said there were a couple?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 There were just a couple - but they only came - periodic
ally, they were not frequent visitors like these friends of my sister and brother you see. They often used to call in you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 When people visited the house would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh perhaps a cup of tea and a biscuit or something like that you know, just a - a snack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would this be on any particular day or occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. Any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you say that the friends invited in were your mother's friends or your father's friends or friends of both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - t
he people - of their age group would be friends of the - of them both. Yes, but of course the others were younger friends of my older brother and sister you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did friends ever call in casually without an invitation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Often. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would this be more or less any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Oh anytime if they just happened to have anything to call about you see they'd just pop in and - and - perhaps used to have a short stay and then go without anything you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would these friends be neighbours as well, would they be living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Not necessarily, no, more so personal friends of my sister and brother who would come in like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Just - only just occasionally that's all but - they - they didn't make a habit of that - you know, going about visiting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends? Would they have music, play games or would they just talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I should think they would just talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I don't think ever such a thought occurred to me. At all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Which group or class would you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I should say the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What were the other sort of people who were in the same class as yourself, what sort of jobs did the parents do would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well they'd be in engineering, it was a - a sort of an industrial you see, they would be in engineering or - there were plenty of mills about, woo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 len mills you know, there'd be - oh they'd be fully employed in the - in the wool}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
en mills and as I say in the engineering - different sections of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What sort of people belonged to the other classes would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you mean the lower classes still or do you mean the upper classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Either lower or upper.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well - I just - just the first thing that comes to mind is - an old gentleman who kept a general grocery stores not far from us and they were really nice family. They were quite friendly as - as the daughter used to pass down to help her fathe
r, you could tell they were really in good circumstances you know. She always used to - I'd be often on - sitting on the step in fact reading a book and she'd often stop and have a work with me, and I really thought they were on a plain above me you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you know the name of those people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Marsden. Mr Marsden his name was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you know any classes }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 who}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  were poorer than your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I don't - I can't recall anybody personally poorer but - there certainly were plenty of very poor people at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Can you remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 being}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 We were never - we were never - made to realize that there was any such thing as distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were you ever told to curtsey or show respect in some other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well, never to curtsey, that would have been the furthest thing from their minds I'm quite sure. But - we did have to be careful how we spoke to older people yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were you ever taught to call anyone sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 In the district who were considered the most important people, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I don't think I was ever aware of anybody b
eing important. No, I don't think so. Just the schoolmistresses you know, we sort of looked up to them as being important. But - or the doctor, we thought he was somebody to be really afraid of. But - apart from that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Who would you say the shopkeepers associated with, who would you say their friends were?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Yes, I can think of a shopkeeper right now and - they actually attended the same church as we did. But - there was never any superior air at all about them and they were just one of the congregation, like anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you say they associated with the people who lived around them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes, I think they would - they were just free and easy sort of with everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 What about the clergy, the vicar at your church, who was he friendly with?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well he seemed to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 befriend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  anybody who needed friendship. I don't think he would have singled anybody out. I mean - actually - that - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 clergy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  actually varied from time to time. But there was a very benevolent old gentleman who was a l
ay preacher at that time and - he was loved by everybody. And he was nice to everybody, there's nobody could have found anything to say against him in any way I'm quite sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What about the teachers, you said that you sort of respected them, would you
 say that the teachers were friends with the working class people or other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I should think - their own profession, members of their o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 wn}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  profession mostly. But - as a child I - I always found them very helpful, if you had the courage to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 approach}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  them. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were there any farmers living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
No, I don't know any farmers - oh, I'm saying I don't know any farmer, now come to think of it there was one farmer cottage not very far away and he did own a few fields round about and there were some cattle at times in those }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 fields.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 He was a farmer in a very small way was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 He must have been, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Who would he be friends with, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I - I haven't the faintest idea. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What about employers, who would your father's employer be friends with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I should think members of his own - - profession, engineering, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 
boiler making}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 , because they were in quite a - a decent size way of business you know. And it was a father and two sons who were - who ran that business you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you say he was friends with other employers in - that line?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I should fancy - I should fancy so. Although he did - always used to seem to have a friendly word for his workmen and he seemed to know them by name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You don't remember him coming into your house for a chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well I don't ever remember him coming in but I do remember often if - if me dad had had a day off work he's called to see if he was all right and if he was coming next day you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 They seemed quite friendly with working class people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What sort of people would you say went to the church and the chapel, would you say they were a different set of people altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, I don't think so, no, it was - the church, it was sort of the centre of the community and everybody went and everybody seemed welcome.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I think there could have been different groups, I think there were some people who were much poorer than we were. I think they must have had a much harder time of life than we had and ours was not - by any means, luxury living. But we had the necessit
ies of life and able to sort of make both ends meet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
You couldn't describe a family within this group could you, the very poor people, you can't think of a family who would fit into that group that you could describe to me and how they lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I - I - no, I couldn't because I was never particularly intimate with anybody like that. But it was - it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 obvious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  even to a small person you see. To a child it was obvious that these people - by the shoes they wore which were badly worn out you see. 
And - holes in their stockings and that kind of thing, it might have been partly due to neglect, you couldn't tell, but - it certainly was there and you wouldn't know what to say accounted for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you think that one group within the working class felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well of course you always get that kind of in a community, you always get the kind of people who think themselves superior even if they're not. But - oh I think that always obtains, even today it does, people - they g
et big ideas about themselves and that's it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Can you think of some people who were like this in your district, who felt themselves a cut above the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well I can't just call anybody to mind by name but - you had a feeling that that kind of thing did exist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable in your area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well, I can't remember any families but I can remember children at school who - did seem definitely rough and who's way you kept out of you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You weren't encouraged to keep out of their way were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh it was just your own feelings. Yes. Absolutely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1575529\charrsid2561303 Do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303  you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. I - I wasn't knowledgeable in that respect at all, I couldn't make any comment on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did your mother and father have - the same attitude to people in different classes? Did they behave in the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 I never heard them make any comment about such things. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well I never suspected it so I - I suppose she would - accepted the circumstances she found herself in and - that was all there was to it and I suppose she made the best of what she'd got which she certainly did as far as her own efforts went you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another and if you can remember anyone who did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, I can't remember anybody who - sort of jumped up out of - that class to - n
o, I can't remember. I mean, at that day there wasn't such things as the pools that people couldn't have a good win on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11959488\charrsid2561303 pools}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
 and lift themselves out of the rut you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember anyone ever being described as a real gentleman or a real lady, and why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Well for one thing the landlord I told you we had, he was a real gentleman. And also - there was a gentleman - we used to buy our coal at that time in a ton and it used to come - a ton at once - and it used to com
e from the pit, straight from the pit. And this gentleman used to come after it had been delivered and collect payment, and I always looked up to him and thought he was absolutely marvellous. He was so gentlemanly. And even - as a young child I could noti
ce his - polish as a man you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would he be a pit owner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
I should think he must have owned that. Yes, he must have had some - financial interest in it even if he didn't own it - solely you see. But he was very well dressed always and - well sp
oken and - and even as a child you could notice that distinction you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you continue to live at home after you left school, you didn't did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No, well you see we left - we left - me father and his second wife. Life was so unpleasant that
 we were better away from them and so my oldest sister got married and we all lived in a nice big house all together. And that's how we got along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you say that starting full time work changed your relationship with your parents at all? Your moth
er was still living when you started work at first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Would you say that it changed your attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Oh no, it didn't make any difference at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 What about with your brothers and sisters, did it alter your attitude to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
No. We were all busy in our own spheres and we were - all very much occupied. All the time. Life was never boring as far as being short of anything to do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you spend your Sunday any differently, did you still go to church morning, afternoon and evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 
Not when I got - not when we got older but we did always - keep contact with church, and then you see, after we were confirmed - we always went for eight o'clock at Sunday morning for the communion service you see. And that - we
 continued - oh - right up to - oh years after I was married and - and then I had a surgical operation and I wasn't able to - go at that early hour. And - I must confess that I dropped off but - I've been going now for some time again. For the communion s
ervice you see. Yes. Oh no, we never severed our relations with the church ever.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you take an interest in politics at this time when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Not when I left school. But I've since become involved in politics since I've been married, 
a little, because me husband's been bound up with politics all his life. And that's why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Do you remember having any particular views in the period between you leaving school and 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Well - there was one thing which struck me very forcibly - wh
en I was young. And I can always remember them - hearing my parents talk about their parents. Now - my mother's father was a miner and he was killed in the pit at the early age of thirty-five. And hearing that talk it impressed me greatly and I always tho
u
ght how dreadful it was to have to go underground working for a living. And running that terrific risk the whole time. And it really did make an impression on me and ever since then I've had sympathy with the miners. And I've always said that people who c
ouldn't pay the price for the coal and who wouldn't or complained, should be made to go and dig their own coal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you have any sympathy towards any political party at that time at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. No, I was never connected with any political party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 How old would you be in 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Twenty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you wouldn't have a vote would you, women didn't get the vote until they were thirty did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Now after - not at that time, but I did have a vote afterwards. After me brother got married me s
ister and I stayed on at that house you see and we had the house in joint names. And I being the older of the two was given a vote. And I used to exercise my vote. I never wasted it. But that was after 1919 you see. Yes. - After me brother got married whi
ch would be in 19 - about 1922.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 So you were never a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you take part in any political activity other than at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 You told me earlier something of how you spent your spare time, doing embroidery and helping at home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Collecting botanical specimens and pressing them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6029762 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3021308 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8864503\charrsid2561303 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way or did you do different things now you'd left school?
